  "prompt": "Why was I blocked from adding questions on quora anonymously and how can I change it?",
  "response": "If you were blocked from adding questions on Quora anonymously, it could be due to several reasons, such as:\n\n1. **Community Guidelines Violations**: If your previous anonymous questions violated Quora's community guidelines (e.g., spam, harassment, or inappropriate content), Quora may have restricted your ability to post anonymously.\n\n2. **Abuse of Anonymous Features**: Quora may have detected misuse of the anonymous feature, such as repeatedly posting harmful or irrelevant content under anonymity.\n\n3. **Account Reputation**: If your account has been flagged or reported multiple times, Quora may limit certain features, including anonymous posting.\n\n4. **Technical Glitch**: Sometimes, the issue could be a technical error or a bug in the system.\n\n### How to Resolve It:\nHere are steps you can take to address the issue:\n\n1. **Review Quora's Policies**: Ensure that your past questions align with Quora's [Community Guidelines](https://www.quora.com/policy/guidelines) and [Terms of Service](https://www.quora.com/about/tos).\n\n2. **Appeal the Restriction**: If you believe the block is a mistake, you can appeal by contacting Quora Support. Go to [Quora Help Center](https://www.quora.com/help) and submit a request explaining your situation.\n\n3. **Improve Account Standing**: If your account has been flagged, focus on posting valuable, high-quality content to rebuild your reputation on the platform.\n\n4. **Check for Technical Issues**: Log out of your account, clear your browser cache, or try using a different device or browser to see if the issue persists.\n\n5. **Use Your Non-Anonymous Identity**: If anonymous posting remains restricted, consider posting questions under your public profile. Anonymous posting is a privilege, and its availability depends on Quora's discretion.\n\nIf the issue isn't resolved, Quora Support is your best resource for further clarification.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
